caption: The food is simply amazing.  Top 2 Mexican restaurants I’ve been too easily.  The drinks are great as well as the prices.  Come for brunch or happy hour you won’t be disappointed.  Let me not forget about the service.  Attentive wait staff makes dining experience a pleasure.

The food was amazing, better than I thought it would be. I recommend the shrimp tacos, steak quesadillas and steak or shrimp fajitas!!! I met two wonderful servers there Milton and Samantha, such a pleasure!! Best servers!! I recommend this place to everyone who wants a Mexican theme restaurant and delicious food!

4pm to 8 pm happy hour margaritas. Closed Sunday.  Sad to say the stress of the pandemic has ruined the management. Having become a regular, had a nice conversation with the waitress, tried to order Chips and Salsa ($ 5.00 ! ) and a happy hour margarita. I was told I had to order the $ 10.00 guacamole at minimum. That isn't the law, that is them taking the "have to order food" order and gouging people using it.  There were plentynof empty tables and I probably would have ordered more but with that attitude, I opted to move on and will not return.  Another one bites the dust. Sad.

The Cochinita Pibil (marinated pork shoulder) was the shining star. 🌟 Very savory and packed full of flavor. The chicken in the chimichanga was very juicy, but the chimichanga exterior itself was a bit soggy. The black beans were well seasoned. The guacamole was good, but not great. It was too watery, and in my opinion, it should be thicker.  Unfortunately, the margaritas were quite terrible. For a place called Margaritas Sunset, I expected better. I'm not even sure what it was composed of, but my regular margarita tasted just like lime Gatorade.  Decent food, terrible drinks, average atmosphere and service.

I ordered a burrito with no beans. I got a burrito with a bunch of beans. I was the only customer too. It was a take out, so I didn’t feel like walking back to return it. I’ll give it a benefit of the doubt, so 3 stars for now, maybe next time I’ll get what I ordered.

I had a few drinks at the bar and ordered 2 chicken lime soup to go. When I got home, the soup was unedible. The lime slices had the rind in the hot soup and made it horribly bitter. I also noticed that the chicken was still on the ribs right before I tossed it in the garbage. This place is too expensive to be eating with my hands and eating it with a spoon just wont work. Im not sure of the logic here. I went back tonite because the bartender is hot and I knew there would be a seat at the bar. It was 2 female bartenders and me in the place. They would not shut up. They just kept blabbing the whole time in spanish. I planned to leave right at closing but they turned on ALL the lights and started sweeping the floor around me! After both girls repeatedly checked to see if I had left payment, I left my unfinished drink never to return. Classy prices, but no class.

Had one of the better Huevos Rancheros (very crispy bacon!!!) and Flan (w/ whipped cream and strawberries) from Mexican places I’ve been too. Great presentation/friendly & attentive staff. Will definitely be coming again, and often!

Too expensive for what is given. Nothing we ordered came with rice and beans. There is much better food just a short walk up or down Graham Avenue. The drinks are also a little small for the price. There are three Mexican places within seven blocks on the same street and this gives the least bang for a buck. We did have a good waitress but we will not be going back only because of her. Btw this is not my first review the others seem like maybe they work there or go out with someone there.

I'd agree with Gabe. Have to decide what vibe they're going for. They have everything they need to be successful but at the prices they charge they need to kick it up a notch. The food was good but not that good. The drinks were OK, but not 3-6 dollars better than a margarita at a dive bar. Service was a little slow too, guess they weren't expecting many people and one person wasn't enough.

Something is amiss with these reviews. I was probably too excited to have a new Mexican restaurant in the neighborhood. There are serviceable options nearby, but both lack the ambiance to sit and drink margaritas, tequila, and beer.  I came here for food and happy hour (and was the only table) which turned into food and sad hour. Their namesake "....Margaritas...." were a huge letdown. I'm willing to pay full price for a margarita with some kick, but since it was happy hour, we ordered happy hour margaritas. Those were basically all sour + some sweet + <1oz of tequila = awful flavor.  The food was fine. The pork shoulder ($18) was tender and flavorful, the mole cheese enchiladas ($14) were spicy and flavorful. HOWEVER, they need to decide if they're an upscale Mexican restaurant, tequila bar, or other. If I'm paying $18 for an 8oz ramekin of pork, the service should be outstanding (same goes for 3 cheese enchiladas on tiny corn tortillas).  The service was abysmal. There were several servers there prepping for a hopefully busy Friday night. They shined the glasses, texted, talked, trained each other how to make cocktails, all while missing several cues from our table. Finally, when I asked for the check, I sat at the table for another 5 or so minutes while they finished shining glasses.  In summary, figure out your identity Las Margaritas Sunset. I can't tell if you're upscale, overpriced, or overrated.

A great variety of Mexican food at this joint, and the portions are pretty big. The meat was juicy and the drinks strong and delicious; I'll definitely stop by here when I'm in the area again. All my friends liked it too which was pretty surprising considering how picky some of them are! Nice place overall.

Chips from the chips and guacamole were a little bland and the guacamole was spicy as advertised.  We got the chicken enchiladas; one Suizas Verdes and the other Mole Poblano. I wasn't crazy about either one of them and I wouldn't order them again. They weren't bad, but they also weren't great.  The tres leches dessert wasnt as soft as you would expect - the milky part was only on the bottom, and the rest was like a regular cake.  They didn't have their liquor license yet, so I'll have to go back to try the margaritas.  I went during the grand opening, so I'm going to give them some time and will revisit my review in a few weeks.

Can't wait to come back and try some margaritas when they get their license!!
